<task id="040" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.H1 — Workspace scoring tests (PriorityScoringService, EffortScoring, WorkspaceMatcher)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>3-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, high-tier, p23-h, bff-api, testing, workspace, scoring</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-H</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Services/Workspace/* test files are disjoint from other H-track batches (Scorecard, Finance, Email, Ai/Safety, Filters, Resilience)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair the HIGH-tier Workspace scoring tests (~3 large files, ~2300 LOC total). Per design.md
    §3.3 HIGH-tier rationale: pure algorithm + safety tests; deterministic; silent bugs cost
    money. These are the highest-value tests in the suite — their defect-prevention value justifies
    careful per-assertion repair rather than archiving.

    Files in scope:
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/PriorityScoringServiceTests.cs` (~772 LOC)
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/EffortScoringTests.cs` (~872 LOC)
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceMatcherTests.cs`

    For each failing test in these files:
    1. Identify the failure (scoring formula change, threshold change, edge-case handling change)
    2. Determine: is the test correct + production drifted? OR is the test stale?
    3. If test is correct + production has a bug: mark `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]`,
       file entry in `ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md`, do NOT touch `src/`
    4. If test is stale: update assertion to match current behavior, mark `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`
    5. Run affected test method; verify Pass (or Skip with reason)

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-040-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every touched test ends in a final end-state.
    `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at project close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist; expert in scoring algorithms + xUnit theory patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    All Workspace scoring tests (PriorityScoringService, EffortScoring, WorkspaceMatcher) end in
    `repaired`, `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. Zero failures in this
    HIGH-tier batch. Real-bug ledger updated for any tests blocked on production fixes.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="target-1">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/PriorityScoringServiceTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-2">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/EffortScoringTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-3">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceMatcherTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="real-bug-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation BEFORE work proceeds</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state trait</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-16">All HIGH-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="HIGH-tier rationale">Defaulting to archive is NOT appropriate here — these tests are defect-prevention load-bearing</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.3 HIGH-tier tests (~35 files total) are pure algorithm + safety: deterministic,
      silent-bug-cost is real money. Workspace scoring (Priority + Effort) drives matter assignment
      and workload distribution; quiet drift here directly affects user-facing prioritization.
      This task is the largest single batch in the HIGH-tier (~2300 LOC across 3 files).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="014" status="not-started">Compile health verified after P1.A batches</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/PriorityScoringServiceTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/EffortScoringTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceMatcherTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">From Phase 0 baseline TRX, list failing tests in the 3 target files.</step>
    <step order="2">For each file: compute pre-edit line count. Read the failing tests and the corresponding production scoring code.</step>
    <step order="3">For each failing test: determine `test-stale` (production behavior is correct but test is hardcoded against old formula) vs `production-bug` (test asserts correct formula but production drifted).</step>
    <step order="4">If any planned file edit would exceed 50% of file lines → HALT, file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-040-{FileName}.md`, await owner approval.</step>
    <step order="5">For `test-stale` cases: update the assertion / theory data to match current formula. Mark `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`.</step>
    <step order="6">For `production-bug` cases: mark test `[Trait("status", "real-bug-pending-fix")]`, add `Skip = "Real bug pending fix - see real-bug-ledger.md entry &lt;ID&gt;"`, add ledger entry with file/line/description/fix-by date.</step>
    <step order="7">After each file: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~&lt;ClassName&gt;"` verify Pass + Skip counts match expectation.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with disposition table per file.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`. Confirm any production bugs are in `real-bug-ledger.md` not `src/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (per-file iterative)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status (verify NFR-01)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/PriorityScoringServiceTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/EffortScoringTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceMatcherTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md (entries if production bugs found)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All Workspace scoring tests Pass or Skip-with-reason; zero Failed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff is &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02); if exceeded, escalation file exists</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has a §6.2 final end-state trait</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Any production bugs identified are filed in `real-bug-ledger.md` with fix-by date</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
## 2026-05-31 — Task 040 completion (Wave 2.1)

**Outcome**: NO-OP. All 3 in-scope files pass with zero failures.

